Product Segmentation Summary
Using Q1 2026 demand, trend direction, stock cover, margin contribution, and supply risk, products are segmented into three stock priority groups:

High Priority (Protect Service & Margin):
Premium skincare and selected premium makeup SKUs in high-demand regions. These drive revenue and margin and currently carry service risk due to low cover and supply delays.

Medium Priority (Standard Control with Monitoring):
Stable-demand skincare and makeup products with adequate cover and moderate margin impact.

Low Priority (Cautious / Lean Stock):
Budget makeup and selected budget skincare SKUs with declining demand and high stock cover, creating overstock and obsolescence risk.

This segmentation supports differentiated stock rules aligned to commercial importance and risk exposure.

High-Priority Products
1. Premium Skincare (All Core Regions – especially East & North)

Highest-margin category.
Strong demand: rising in North and sharply rising in East.
Critically low cover:
East: 4 days cover + 7-day delayed shipment
North: 5 days cover, no incoming stock
Stable but important in South and West (11–12 days cover).
Service Risk: Immediate risk of stockouts in East and North.
Business Impact: Direct margin loss and reputational risk in growth markets.

2. Premium Makeup – North & East

Strong and rising demand in both regions.
Low to moderate cover (North: 10 days, East: 9 days).
Important for brand positioning and revenue growth.
Service Risk: Moderate, especially if demand continues rising.

Conclusion:
Premium skincare (all regions, especially East/North) and Premium makeup (North/East) should receive highest service level targets and replenishment priority.

Medium-Priority Products
1. Premium Makeup – South & West

Stable demand.
Adequate cover (14–15 days).
Good margin contribution but lower urgency.
2. Budget Skincare – North & East

Stable demand.
18–22 days cover (healthy range).
Important for presence and volume, especially in price-sensitive markets.
3. Premium Skincare – South & West

Stable/unstable but not high growth.
11–12 days cover (acceptable but should not reduce further).
Conclusion:
Managed under normal replenishment rules, with forecast review but no emergency action required.

Low-Priority Products
1. Budget Makeup – All Major Regions

Falling demand in North, South, West; stable but weak in East.
High cover levels (25–34 days).
Clear overstock risk.
